# =============================================================================
# SIGIL ARTIFACT MODEL
# =============================================================================
# Sigil artifacts fall into three categories:
#
# 1. SHARED (tracked): Team taste, curated references, survival metrics
#    - sigil-mark/*.md, sigil-mark/moodboard/*.md
#    - .sigil/survival.json, .sigil/seed.yaml, .sigil/eras/
#
# 2. MACHINE-GENERATED (ignored): Rebuilds automatically
#    - .sigil/workshop.json, .sigil/craft-log/
#
# 3. USER-SPECIFIC (ignored): Local experimentation, raw assets
#    - sigil-mark/moodboard/sandbox/, raw images
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .sigil/ Machine-Generated State
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These files are generated per-session or rebuild automatically.
# They should not be committed to version control.

# Workshop index (pre-computed, rebuilds on package/import changes)
.sigil/workshop.json

# Craft logs (session-specific debugging, per-developer)
.sigil/craft-log/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .sigil/ Shared State (TRACKED - do not add to gitignore)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These files ARE tracked and shared with the team:
# - .sigil/survival.json      # Pattern tracking (team consensus)
# - .sigil/survival-stats.json # Component metrics (team visibility)
# - .sigil/seed.yaml          # Virtual Sanctuary taste (team direction)
# - .sigil/pending-ops.json   # CI/CD queue (team operations)
# - .sigil/eras/              # Historical record (team memory)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Moodboard Sandbox (User-Specific Experimentation)
